**2) What\'s the main question being asked or hypothesis being tested in
this study?**

We seek to ascertain that public punitiveness is positively correlated
with numerous dependent measures (listed in section 3) which, from a
normative point of view, should be correlated negatively (or not at
all).

All factors will be correlated with the punitiveness construct -- which
will be comprised of the following judgments and beliefs \--

-   Belief in more punishment

-   The Benthamite principle of parsimony --R

-   Support for three strike laws

-   Support for life in prison without the possibility of parole

-   Support for the death penalty

-   A sentencing decision in a second degree murder case

